<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" type="diagnosis and remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">Diagnosis and remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">
The report of this species is a new distribution record to Wuyi Mountains and had been redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Qian, Y. H." journalOrPublisher="Journal of Insect Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" pagination="1 - 9" refId="B7867316" refString="Qian, Y. H., Du, Y. Z., 2012. A new stonefly species, Rhopalopsole tricuspis (Leuctridae: Plecoptera), and three new records of stoneflies from the Qinling Mountains of Shaanxi, China. Journal of Insect Science 12 (47): 1 - 9" title="A new stonefly species, Rhopalopsole tricuspis (Leuctridae: Plecoptera), and three new records of stoneflies from the Qinling Mountains of Shaanxi, China" volume="12" year="2012">Qian and Du (2012b)</bibRefCitation>
. Head dark brown at upper half, brown at lower half, wider than pronotum; ocelli brown; antennae and palpi light brown; pronotum light brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F8002508" captionText="Figure 12. Rhopalopsole basinigra Yang &amp; Yang, 1995. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711856" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">12</figureCitation>
A). Epiproct thick at base, expanding in top view, ending in a shallow trilobed tip.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
